{"word":"H359 - אֵילֹות - ʼÊylôwth - ay-loth' - Elath","slug":"H359","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אֵילֹות</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼÊylôwth"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ay-loth'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Elath"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05D9;&#x05DC;&#x05EA;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &#x05D0;&#x05D9;&#x05DC;&#x05D5;&#x05EA; - 'e&#x0302;ylo&#x0302;th  'e&#x0302;ylath</b> - <i>ay-loth', ay-lath'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H352\">H352</a>; <i>trees</i> or a <i>grove</i> (that is, palms); <i>Eloth</i> or <i>Elath</i>, a place on the Red Sea: - Elath, Eloth."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H193\">H193</a>, <a href=\"#/H195\">H195</a>, <a href=\"#/H197\">H197</a>, <a href=\"#/H198\">H198</a>, <a href=\"#/H352\">H352</a>, <a href=\"#/H354\">H354</a>, <a href=\"#/H355\">H355</a>, <a href=\"#/H356\">H356</a>, <a href=\"#/H357\">H357</a>, <a href=\"#/H361\">H361</a>, <a href=\"#/H362\">H362</a>, <a href=\"#/H364\">H364</a>, <a href=\"#/H365\">H365</a>, <a href=\"#/H424\">H424</a>, <a href=\"#/H425\">H425</a>, <a href=\"#/H436\">H436</a>, <a href=\"#/H440\">H440</a>"}]}